abstract: Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau said on Thursday that the U.S. government should not finalize a trade deal with China unless the pact also secured the release of two Canadians detained by Beijing.
snippet: Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau said on Thursday that the U.S. government should not finalize a trade deal with China unless the pact also secured the release of two Canadians detained by Beijing.
lead_paragraph: OTTAWA — Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau said on Thursday that the U.S. government should not finalize a trade deal with China unless the pact also secured the release of two Canadians detained by Beijing.
headline_main: U.S. Should Not Finalize China Trade Deal Unless Detained Canadians Are Released: Trudeau
headline_print_headline: U.S. Should Not Finalize China Trade Deal Unless Detained Canadians Are Released: Trudeau

abstract: BMW AG and Daimler AG said Wednesday they plan to exit the North American car-sharing market, with the joint venture partners halting operations in Montreal, New York, Seattle, Washington, D.C., and Vancouver, as they focus on the European market.
snippet: BMW AG and Daimler AG said Wednesday they plan to exit the North American car-sharing market, with the joint venture partners halting operations in Montreal, New York, Seattle, Washington, D.C., and Vancouver, as they focus on the European market.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — BMW AG and Daimler AG said Wednesday they plan to exit the North American car-sharing market, with the joint venture partners halting operations in Montreal, New York, Seattle, Washington, D.C., and Vancouver, as they focus on the European market.
headline_main: Daimler, BMW Exiting North American Car-Sharing Market, Cutting in Europe
headline_print_headline: Daimler, BMW Exiting North American Car-Sharing Market, Cutting in Europe

abstract: Nestle said on Thursday it had agreed to sell a majority stake in Herta, its packaged meat business, to family-run Spanish company Casa Tarradellas to create a joint venture.

headline_main: Nestle to Sell 60% of Herta Meats to Casa Tarradellas to Create JV

abstract: Starbucks Corp agreed on Thursday to pay restitution and accept greater oversight to settle a multi-year probe finding that it had illegally required New York City employees to find substitutes when they needed to use sick leave.

lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Starbucks Corp agreed on Thursday to pay restitution and accept greater oversight to settle a multi-year probe finding that it had illegally required New York City employees to find substitutes when they needed to use sick leave.
headline_main: Starbucks Settles New York Probe Into Illegal Sick Leave Policy

abstract: The U.S. House of Representatives overwhelmingly approved a new North American trade deal on Thursday that includes tougher labor and automotive content rules but leaves $1.2 trillion in annual U.S.-Mexico-Canada trade flows largely unchanged.
